pull.title: Fix torcontrol.cpp unused private field warning
pull.body:
Should solve the following warning, though I think the warning could be a false positive because of the constructor initialization (`orController::TorController(struct event_base* base, const std::string& target):
    base(base)`):

`torcontrol.cpp:365:24: warning: private field 'base' is not used [-Wunused-private-field]`

issue.title: Net backports
issue.body:
Backports of spelling fixes and changes to netbase that bring us closer to 0.13.0 for it and torcontrol.cpp.

Main API change is to move towards storage-only structures for basic network concepts, and splitting out DNS lookup.  In later changes in Core CNetAddr moves to its own file netaddress.cpp.

bitcoin#7313
bitcoin#7329
bitcoin#7683
bitcoin#7570
bitcoin#7868
+ BU-specific changes
